<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>{{pageTitle}}</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400;1,500&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header class="site-header">
        <nav class="nav-container">
            <a href="/" class="logo">
                <span class="logo-icon">+</span>
                <span class="logo-text">Faithful Word</span>
            </a>
            <ul class="nav-links">
                <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
                <li><a href="/posts/new" class="btn-write">Write</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <main class="main-content">
        <section class="about-section">
            <h1 class="about-title">About Faithful Word</h1>
            
            <div class="about-content">
                <p class="about-lead">
                    Faithful Word exists to strengthen believers through Scripture-centered reflection 
                    and thoughtful teaching. We believe that God's Word is living and active, and that 
                    through careful study and meditation, we grow closer to Christ.
                </p>

                <blockquote class="about-verse">
                    "All Scripture is breathed out by God and profitable for teaching, for reproof, 
                    for correction, and for training in righteousness, that the man of God may be 
                    complete, equipped for every good work."
                    <cite>2 Timothy 3:16-17</cite>
                </blockquote>

                <h2>Our Purpose</h2>
                <p>
                    In a world filled with noise and distraction, we seek to provide a quiet space 
                    for reflection. Our posts are not meant to be consumed quickly, but to be read 
                    slowly, considered carefully, and applied prayerfully.
                </p>
                <p>
                    We write about faith, theology, prayer, Christian living, and spiritual growth. 
                    Our aim is not to present novel ideas, but to faithfully communicate the timeless 
                    truths of Scripture in a way that speaks to the challenges and questions of our day.
                </p>

                <h2>Our Convictions</h2>
                <ul class="convictions-list">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Scripture is our authority.</strong> We believe the Bible is the inspired, 
                        inerrant Word of God, and the final authority for faith and practice.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Christ is central.</strong> Every post ultimately points to Jesus Christ, 
                        who is the way, the truth, and the life.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Grace transforms.</strong> We write not to condemn, but to encourage. 
                        The gospel is good news for sinners saved by grace.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Community matters.</strong> While this blog is a resource, it is not a 
                        replacement for the local church. We encourage all believers to be rooted in 
                        a faithful, Bible-teaching congregation.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Join the Conversation</h2>
                <p>
                    We invite you to read, reflect, and respond. If a post stirs your heart or 
                    challenges your thinking, share it with others. If you have been blessed by 
                    what God is teaching you, consider contributing your own reflections.
                </p>
                <p>
                    May the Lord use this humble effort for His glory and the building up of His church.
                </p>

                <p class="about-closing">
                    <em>"Not to us, O Lord, not to us, but to your name give glory, 
                    for the sake of your steadfast love and your faithfulness."</em>
                    <br>
                    <span class="about-reference">Psalm 115:1</span>
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer">
        <div class="footer-content">
            <div class="footer-brand">
                <span class="logo-icon">+</span>
                <span class="logo-text">Faithful Word</span>
            </div>
            <p class="footer-verse">"But grow in the grace and knowledge of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ. To him be the glory both now and to the day of eternity."</p>
            <p class="footer-reference">2 Peter 3:18</p>
            <p class="footer-copyright">Built with faith.</p>
        </div>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
